    "explanation": "<p>Given,</p>\n<p>$$I = \\int {{{{e^x}} \\over {{e^{4x}} + {e^{2x}} + 1}}dx} $$</p>\n<p>$$J = \\int {{{{e^{ - x}}} \\over {{e^{ - 4x}} + {e^{ - 2x}} + 1}}dx = \\int {{{{e^{3x}}} \\over {{e^{4x}} + {e^{2x}} + 1}}dx} } $$</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ $$J - I = \\int {{{{e^x}({e^{2x}} - 1)} \\over {{e^{4x}} + {e^{2x}} + 1}}dx} $$</p>\n<p>Let $${e^x} = t \\Rightarrow {e^x}dx = dt$$</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ $$J - I = \\int {{{{t^2} - 1} \\over {{t^4} + {t^2} + 1}}dt} $$</p>\n<p>$$ = \\int {{{1 - {1 \\over {{t^2}}}} \\over {{t^2} + 1 + {1 \\over {{t^2}}}}}dt} $$</p>\n<p>Let, $$t + {1 \\over t} = u \\Rightarrow \\left( {1 - {1 \\over {{t^2}}}} \\right)dt = du$$</p>\n<p>$$J - I = \\int {{{du} \\over {{u^2} - 1}} = {1 \\over 2}\\log \\left| {{{u - 1} \\over {u + 1}}} \\right| + C} $$</p>\n<p>$$ = {1 \\over 2}\\log \\left| {{{{{{t^2} + 1} \\over t} - 1} \\over {{{{t^2} + 1} \\over t} + 1}}} \\right| + C$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {1 \\over 2}\\log \\left| {{{{e^{2x}} - {e^x} + 1} \\over {{e^{2x}} + {e^x} + 1}}} \\right| + C$$</p>",
